{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2018}} {{Infobox film | name = Black, White & Blue | image = | caption = Theatrical release poster | director = Asia Norris | producer = {{Plainlist| * Curtis Scoon * Luc Stephen }} | writer = | based on = | starring = {{Plainlist| * [[Charlamagne tha God]] * [[Michael Dowd (police officer)|Michael Dowd]] * Karen Dumas * [[Michael Eric Dyson]] * [[Ibrahim Hooper]] * [[Killer Mike]] * Leslie Mathews * [[Lord Jamar]] * Honorable [[William "Billy" Murphy Jr.]] * [[Touré (journalist)|Touré]] * [[Coleman Young II]] }} | music = | cinematography = | editing = | production companies = | distributor = | released = {{Film date|2018|1|19|[[Sundance Film Festival]]|2018|2|2|United States}} | runtime = 76 minutes<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.deadlinedetroit.com/articles/19032/trailer_black_white_blue_documentary_on_race_in_america_to_debut_in_detroit |title=Trailer: 'Black, White & Blue' Documentary on Race in America To Debut in Detroit |last=Lengel|first=Allan|date=January 2, 2018|website= |publisher=Deadline Detroit|access-date=January 25, 2018|quote=}}</ref> | country = United States | language = English | budget = $175,000 <ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.imdb.com/title/tt6850778/|title= Black White & Blue (2018)|last= |first= |date=January 19, 2018 |website= |publisher=IMDB |access-date=January 25, 2018|quote=}}</ref> | gross = }}
'''''Black, White & Blue''''' is a 2018 American [[documentary film]] directed by Asia Norris and produced by Curtis Scoon.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.imdb.com/title/tt6850778/|title= Black White & Blue (2018)|last= |first= |date=January 19, 2018 |website= |publisher=IMDB |access-date=January 25, 2018|quote=}}</ref> The film covers the history of race related issues in America<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.localdvm.com/news/i-270/local-documentary-creates-buzz-on-hot-topics-in-the-nation/887567283|title=Local documentary creates buzz on hot topics in the nation|last=Grimshaw|first=Shennekia|date=December 26, 2017|website= |publisher=WDVM|access-date=January 25, 2018|quote=}}</ref> and features [[Michigan]] Senator [[Coleman Young II]], television personality [[Charlamagne tha God]], rapper [[Killer Mike]] and [[Lord Jamar]] from [[Brand Nubian]].
''Black, White & Blue'' premiered at the [[Sundance Film Festival]], on January 19, 2018, and will have a special advance screenings on February 2, 2018, at the [[Charles H. Wright Museum of African-American History]] in [[Detroit, Michigan]]. A second screening is scheduled in [[Silver Spring, Maryland]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://metro-dc.com/events/view/eb/41683890639 |title=‘Black, White & Blue’|last= |first= |date= |website= |publisher=Metro DC|access-date=January 25, 2018|quote=}}</ref>
==Synopsis== ''Black, White & Blue'' discusses the history of race related issues in America in one-on-one interviews with notable African-American's, including: Michigan Senator [[Coleman Young II]], [[Baltimore]] Circuit Court Judge [[William "Billy" Murphy Jr.]], journalist [[Touré (journalist)|Touré]], author [[Michael Eric Dyson]], [[Detroit News]] reporter James David Dickson, activist [[Ibrahim Hooper]], rapper [[Killer Mike]], [[Lord Jamar]] from [[Brand Nubian]], former [[NYPD]] Officer [[Michael Dowd (police officer)|Michael Dowd]], along with interviews with the “man on the street” and visuals from across the country.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://michronicleonline.com/2018/01/18/distinguished-new-documentary-black-white-blue-to-premier-at-the-wright/ |title=Distinguished new documentary, ‘Black White & Blue,’ to premier at the Wright |last=Edward|first=Roz|date= |website= |publisher=Michigan Chronicle|access-date=January 25, 2018|quote=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.blacknews.com/news/independent-documentary-black-white-blue-critically-examines-race-police-brutality-presidential-election/ |title=Independent Documentary “Black White & Blue” Critically Examines Race, Police Brutality and America’s 2016 Presidential Election|last= |first= |date=May 12, 2017|website= |publisher=Black News|access-date=January 25, 2018|quote=}}</ref>
Topics discussed in the documentary include: the [[Black Lives Matter Movement]], the [[Flint Water Crisis]], and violence between law enforcement and citizens.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://srmagonline.com/2017/05/15/black-white-blue-takes-a-look-at-race-and-police-brutality/ |title=New Documentary "Black White & Blue" Takes a Look at Race and Police Brutality|last=Dixon|first=Danielle|date=May 15, 2017|website= |publisher=Soul Reflectionz Magazine|access-date=January 25, 2018|quote=}}</ref>
