{{Infobox Sculpture | image = [[Image:Chagall Four Seasons 060514.jpg|300 px]] | title = Four Seasons | artist = [[Marc Chagall]] | year = 1974 | height_metric = | city = [[Chicago]] | museum = [[Chase Tower (Chicago)|Chase Tower Plaza]] }} '''''Four Seasons''''' is a [[mosaic]] by [[Marc Chagall]] that is located in [[Chase Tower (Chicago)|Chase Tower Plaza]] in the [[Chicago Loop|Loop]] district of [[Chicago]], [[Illinois]]. The mosaic was a gift to the City of Chicago by [[Frederick H. Prince]] (via the Prince Charitable Trusts); it is wrapped around four sides of a {{convert|70|ft|m}} long, {{convert|14|ft|m}} high, {{convert|10|ft|m}} wide rectangular box, and was dedicated on September 27, 1974.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.chipublib.org/004chicago/timeline/chagall.html |title=Chagall: Four Seasons |accessdate=2007-08-05 |publisher=[[Chicago Public Library]] }}</ref> It was renovated in 1994 and a protective glass canopy was installed.<ref>{{cite web |first= Mary Ann |last=Sullivan |url=http://www.bluffton.edu/~sullivanm/chagall/chagall.html |title=Four Seasons |accessdate=2007-08-05 |work=Digital Imaging Project }}</ref>
The mosaic was the subject of a 1974 documentary film, ''The Gift: Four Seasons Mosaic of Marc Chagall'', directed by [[Chuck Olin]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0480393/ |title=The Gift: Four Seasons Mosaic of Marc Chagall |accessdate=2007-08-05 |work=[[IMDB]] }}</ref>
