{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2015}} {{Infobox artist | name = Loris Cecchini | image =Loris Cecchini.jpg | imagesize = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = 1969 | birth_place = [[Milan]], Italy | death_date = | death_place = | nationality = Italian | field = [[Contemporary art]] | training = | movement = Sculpture, [[Installation art|Installation]] | works = | influenced by = | influenced = | awards = | website = {{url|loriscecchini.org}} }}
'''Loris Cecchini''' (born 1969) is an Italian [[contemporary art]]ist. He works in various media, among them [[sculpture]], [[installation (art)|installation]] and [[photography]].{{r|moma}} In 2014 he won the annual Premio Arnaldo Pomodoro per la Scultura awarded by the [[Fondazione Arnaldo Pomodoro]].{{r|fap}}
Cecchini was born in [[Milan]], in [[Lombardy]] in northern Italy, in 1969.{{r|fap}} He studied in [[Siena]], in [[Florence]] and in Milan.{{r|moma}} His work was shown at the [[Museo Civico di Castel Nuovo]] in [[Naples]] in 2000,{{r|marco}} at [[MoMA PS1]] in New York in 2006–2007,{{r|moma}} and at the [[Musée d'Art Moderne de Saint-Etienne Métropole]] in [[Saint-Étienne]] in France in 2010.{{r|mam}} As winner of the 2014 Premio Arnaldo Pomodoro per la Scultura, he had a solo show at the premises of the Fondazione in Milan in March of that year.{{r|fap}}
